# Azveria Online Admin Guide

This document defines admin-only behavior in the Azveria Online web app.

## Admin Navigation

### Announcements
- View global announcement history.
- Send new global announcements.
- Player accounts can read but cannot post.

### Nation Editor
- Right panel nation selector + search.
- Center panel editable nation state.
- Save: commits changes to selected nation.
- Cancel: reverts unsaved values to snapshot from select-time.
- Supports creating placeholder (dummy) nations with full editable stats.

### Account Management / Player Deletion
- Delete Player now supports two modes:
	- Standard delete: removes the player account and owned nation records.
	- Delete + purge player data: also removes player-linked app artifacts (such as map editor political references and topbar user overrides).
- This purge option is available as a checkbox in the Delete Player Account area.
- Safety confirmation: when purge mode is enabled, admin must also type `PURGE PLAYER DATA` before deletion is accepted.

### Map
- View and pan/zoom all map layers.
- Upload replacement images for:
	- Main map
	- Terrain map
	- Political map
- Map editor now uses Draft and Active states:
	- `Save Draft` stores in-progress editor changes without affecting players.
	- `Undo` is available while editing draft maps (button or `Ctrl+Z` / `Cmd+Z`).
	- Draft saves no longer run nation terrain-stat sync, so saving is much faster for large maps.
	- `Preview Active` shows the currently live map.
	- `Resume Draft` returns to the saved draft for editing.
	- `Set Draft Active` publishes the draft map to all players and then runs nation terrain-stat sync.
- Note to move while drawing hold shift and click and drag to move the map.
- Map editor now shows a live `Save payload` indicator near save/status.
	- This is an estimated JSON size for map editor state saves.
	- Color guide:
		- Normal: below ~2 MB
		- Warning: ~2 MB to ~8 MB
		- High risk: above ~8 MB
	- If payload is high, simplify/reduce stored stroke history before saving.
	- Large payloads can increase save time or fail if infrastructure limits are exceeded.

### Chat
- Access all chats.
- Create/delete group chats.
- Add/remove members in group chats.
- Direct message any player.

### Combat (Battle Tab)
- View a full combat snapshot for any player nation.
- Select target player from the admin player dropdown in the Orders panel.
- See commanders and all units with:
	- Base unit name
	- Separate row/card for each owned unit instance (no grouped shared stats)
	- Editable custom name
	- Editable class/status/race/terrain
	- Effective statline (ATK, DEF, DMG, HP, MVT, RNG, ACT)
	- Unit rating
	- Admin note per unit instance
	- Army rating breakdown math
- View and moderate submitted combat orders from players.

#### Quick Reference
| Goal | Where | Action | Result |
|---|---|---|---|
| Review a player's battle setup | Combat -> Orders panel | Select player from dropdown | Commanders, units, ratings, and orders load for that player |
| Edit unit combat identity | Unit card -> edit fields | Update name/class/status/race/terrain, then Save Unit | Unit override metadata updates immediately |
| Edit core stats | Unit card -> stat fields | Change ATK/DEF/DMG/HP/MVT/RNG/ACT, then Save Unit | Effective stats and computed rating refresh |
| Add per-unit admin notes | Unit card -> Admin Note | Enter notes and Save Unit | Note is saved to that specific unit instance only |
| Force a specific unit rating | Unit card -> Rating | Enter explicit rating, then Save Unit | Final rating uses override instead of formula |
| Return to formula-driven rating | Unit card -> Rating | Clear Rating field, then Save Unit | Final rating reverts to formula output |
| Rebalance globally | Combat -> Rating Formula | Edit equation, preview results, then Apply Formula | All non-overridden unit ratings recalculate |
| Verify rating math | Unit card -> Army Rating Breakdown | Expand breakdown details | See inputs, expression, evaluated value, rounding, and final rating source |
| Moderate battle orders | Orders list | Set pending/approved/denied and add note | Player order status and review note are persisted |
| Control intel sharing | Nation Editor -> Nation Visibility Matrix | Toggle Army Rating visibility per viewer/subject | Army rating shown or hidden in Other Nations |

#### Combat Snapshot Panels
- **Commanders panel**:
	- Contains all units flagged as commander from unit catalog metadata.
	- Shows total army rating for the selected nation at the top.
- **Units panel**:
	- Shows the same data model as commanders, for non-commander units.
	- Cards are expandable to inspect stats and breakdown details.
- **Orders panel**:
	- Admin player selector
	- Combat order queue with review controls
- **Rating Formula section**:
	- Dedicated admin formula editor (separate from Orders)
	- Help bubble with field-by-field meanings and formula flow

#### Direct Admin Unit Editing
Admin can edit unit data inline and save per unit with **Save Unit**.

Editable fields:
- `Unit Name` (custom name)
- `Class`
- `Status`
- `Race`
- `Terrain`
- `ATK`, `DEF`, `DMG`, `HP`, `MVT`, `RNG`, `ACT`
- `Rating` (optional explicit override)
- `Admin Note` (private per-unit-instance note)

Behavior details:
- Each owned unit is listed as its own instance card in Combat.
- Saving one instance updates only that instance (for example HP battle damage), not all copies.
- If `Rating` is blank, rating is computed from the formula.
- If `Rating` is set, that value overrides formula output for final unit rating.
- Effective class/status/race/terrain are treated as combat metadata and saved as unit overrides.

#### Army Rating Formula (Admin-Configurable)
The combat tab now includes an editable **equation field** for rating math.

Default formula:

```
HP*DEF + (ATK+DEF)(MVT+RNG) + ACT(ATK*DMG)
```

Final rating behavior:
- Evaluate the formula result.
- Round down the final formula value with `floor(...)`.
- If a unit has a manual rating override, override still wins as final rating.

Supported formula syntax:
- Variables: `ATK`, `DEF`, `DMG`, `HP`, `MVT`, `RNG`, `ACT`
- Operators: `+`, `-`, `*`, `/`, `(`, `)`
- Implicit multiplication is supported:
	- `ACT(ATK+DMG)`
	- `(ATK+DEF)(MVT+RNG)`

Admin safety/apply flow:
1. Edit formula in the equation field.
2. Use **Preview Formula** before applying.
3. Apply formula with a 3-step confirmation flow.
4. Final step requires typing: `APPLY RATING FORMULA`.

Preview options available in Combat:
- Preview using a selected existing unit instance (real unit stats).
- Preview using manually entered stat values.

#### Army Rating Breakdown
Each unit card includes an **Army Rating Breakdown** section showing:
- Raw stat inputs
- Formula string used
- Normalized/evaluated expression
- Raw formula result
- Rounding mode (`floor`)
- Formula rating
- Final rating (and whether override was applied)

Example breakdown:
- Inputs: `ATK=12`, `DEF=8`, `DMG=10`, `HP=15`, `MVT=5`, `RNG=3`, `ACT=2`
- Formula: `HP*DEF + (ATK+DEF)(MVT+RNG) + ACT(ATK*DMG)`
- Evaluated: `15*8 + (12+8)*(5+3) + 2*(12*10)`
- Raw result: `520`
- Formula rating: `floor(520) = 520`

#### Total Army Rating
Total army rating is shown:
- At the top of Combat for selected nation
- On the Player dashboard
- In Other Nations (when allowed by visibility)

Current aggregation behavior:
- `total_army_rating = sum(unit_rating * unit_qty)` across commander + unit rows.

#### Combat Order Moderation
Player-submitted combat orders appear in admin Orders panel.
Each order supports:
- `pending` / `approved` / `denied` status
- Optional review note

Review updates are persisted and visible back to players.

#### Visibility Matrix: Army Rating Option
In **Nation Editor -> Nation Visibility Matrix**, admins can now toggle:
- `Army Rating`

If disabled for a viewer->subject pair:
- Subject nation's army rating is hidden in Other Nations.

#### Practical Workflow Example
1. Open Combat tab as admin.
2. Choose a player from the selector.
3. Inspect total army rating and commander/unit cards.
4. Expand a unit.
5. Edit class/status/race/terrain and stat fields.
6. (Optional) set explicit rating override.
7. Click **Save Unit**.
8. Expand Army Rating Breakdown to verify math.
9. Edit formula equation in right panel and run Preview.
10. Apply formula with 3-step confirmation and re-check unit/army ratings.
11. Review player combat orders and set status + note.

#### Data Storage Notes
- Unit combat overrides are stored on `nation_units.stats_override_json`.
- Per-user player settings remain in `user_settings`.
- Combat rating formula config is global and stored in app storage JSON.

#### API Surface (Combat/Battle)
Admin:
- `GET /api/admin/combat/snapshot?user_id={id}`
- `GET /api/admin/combat/orders?user_id={id}`
- `PUT /api/admin/combat/orders/{notificationId}/status`
- `PUT /api/admin/combat/units/{nationUnitId}/stats`
- `GET /api/admin/combat/rating-config`
- `PUT /api/admin/combat/rating-config`

Player:
- `GET /api/me/combat/snapshot`
- `GET /api/me/combat/orders`
- `POST /api/me/combat/orders`
- `PATCH /api/me/units/{unitId}/name`

#### Guardrails and Recommended Admin Practices
- Prefer formula tuning over frequent hard rating overrides.
- Use rating overrides for exceptional lore/hero units only.
- Keep class/status/race/terrain values consistent with your campaign taxonomy.
- Review army rating visibility defaults before major wars to avoid information leaks.

